# How I made the game

I looked up a hangman game using python and found one which I used as a template/tutorial on it from which I edited the file to my liking to make it more my style and a more robust game.

(Website used: [http://www.pythonforbeginners.com/code-snippets-source-code/game-hangman](http://www.pythonforbeginners.com/code-snippets-source-code/game-hangman) )

# File Structure

File structure is an important part to any program as it defines where to look for certain files and helps the code structure its location for finding dependencies.

The way I have done this is having the executable files in the base folder and they will look for the python file in data which includes the dependency for the game to work (the word list for hangman in this case which is also a hidden file so it is harder to edit but still can be edited if need be) and added an installation files folder for python which is needed to run the batch file properly.

# Problem Solving

I could type all the letters and it would only take it as 1 guess

To solve it I restricted the input to 1 letter at a time and if you tried to put 2 or more letters it would end the game calling you a cheater.

# Creating the executable file

I found a few ways to try to make an executable however none of them worked in the sense that it couldn&#39;t open without a window, I intended it to run using command prompt or terminal for mac users, the way witch I solved this was by making a Batch file and a Command file to have a run.bat/run.command file run the game in command prompt and terminal.

# How to send the program to others

The way I made it so that I could transfer the program to others is I zipped the files which both compresses it and keeps it as a single file making it easier to keep organised as well.

(hangmangame.py)

import time

import random

# welcoming the user

name = input(&quot;What be yarr name? &quot;)

print(&quot;Aye, &quot; + name, &quot;ye be running outta time, the hangmans noose be ready around your neck, solve this word and ye be free.&quot;)

print(&quot;&quot;)

# wait for 1 second

time.sleep(1)

print(&quot;Ye best start guessing...&quot;)

time.sleep(0.5)

# here we set the secret

lines = open(&quot;words.txt&quot;).read()

line = lines[0:]

word = line.split()

myword = random.choice(word)

# creates an variable with an empty value

guesses = &#39;&#39;

# determine the number of turns

turns = 10

# Create a while loop

# check if the turns are more than zero

while turns &gt; 0:

    # make a counter that starts with zero

    failed = 0

    # for every character in word

    for char in myword:

        # see if the character is in the players guess

        if char in guesses:

            # print then out the character

            print(char,)

        else:

            # if not found, print a dash

            print(&quot;\_&quot;,)

        # and increase the failed counter with one

            failed += 1

    #  if failed is equal to zero

    #  print(You Won

    if failed == 0:

        print(&quot;Ye be living for now&quot;)

# exit the script

        break

    print

#  ask the user go guess a character

    guess = input(&quot;guess a letter: &quot;)

#  checks the input for more than 1 character after return is pressed and will end the game for the user

    if len(guess) &gt; 1:

        print(&quot;Ye can&#39;t be cheatin&#39; now, ye be strung up for it now.&quot;)

        exit()

#  set the players guess to guesses

    guesses += guess

#  if the guess is not found in the word

    if guess not in myword:

        # turns counter decreases with 1 (now 9)

        turns -= 1

    #  print wrong for failed letter

        print(&quot;Wrong&quot;)

    #  how many turns are left

        print(&quot;Ye have&quot;, + turns, &#39;more guesses&#39;)

    #  if the turns are equal to zero

        if turns == 0:

            # print the losing quote

            print(&quot;Ye be hanging&quot;)
